Statistics-Probability:

(Learning outcome: You will be able to create and analyze distribution of variables, apply the rules of probability to determine the likelihood of an event, use a sample to infer or draw conclusions about the population from what it is drawn.)
https://oli.cmu.edu/courses/probability-statistics-open-free/ (comprehensive online course)
https://www.khanacademy.org/math/statistics-probability (beginner-friendly)
http://web.stanford.edu/class/cs224n/readings/cs229-prob.pdf (detailed review of the principles of probability theory)

Linear Algebra:

(Learning outcome: You will able to learn about topics like vectors and spaces, Matrix Transformation, Alternate coordinate systems(bases))

https://www.khanacademy.org/math/linear-algebra (beginner-friendly)
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZHQObOWTQDPD3MizzM2xVFitgF8hE_ab
(The videos allow beginners to begin the linear algebra series with basics)
https://www.deeplearningbook.org/contents/linear_algebra.html
(By grasping the concepts of linear algebra, it will be essential for understanding and working with many machine learning algorithms.)
https://github.com/fastai/numerical-linear-algebra/blob/master/README.md(Computational Linear Algebra Course for coders)
https://www.coursera.org/specializations/mathematics-machine-learning(Self-paced online course provided by Coursera with flexible schedule)
https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/mathematics/18-06-linear-algebra-spring-2010/index.htm(MIT Linear Algebra course, highly comprehensive)

Calculus:

https://www.khanacademy.org/math/multivariable-calculus (Beginner-friendly)
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZHQObOWTQDMsr9K-rj53DwVRMYO3t5Yr
(This video series covers important topics of calculus that are required in Data Science.)
https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/mathematics/18-01sc-single-variable-calculus-fall-2010/?fbclid=IwAR0LKFiV32uCutWWaDFj2J-be7kbt3S6UvXjYqd3Iml_ofwTHMXE96y4m3U
(This MIT Single Variable Calculus course covers differentiation and integration of function of functions of one variable, and ends with infinite series.)
https://ocw.mit.edu/courses/mathematics/18-02sc-multivariable-calculus-fall-2010/
(This MIT Multivariable Calculus course contains differential, integral and vector calculus for functions of more than one variable.)

Decision Theory:

http://probability.ca/jeff/ftpdir/anjali0.pdf (highly comprehensive)
https://mitpress.mit.edu/books/introduction-statistical-decision-theory
